{"number":56965,"title":"[BUG] Keyvault Keys from mHSM are returning Null Encoded Policies","body":"### Library name and version

Azure.Security.KeyVault.Keys 4.9.0

### Describe the bug

After retrieving a key from mHSM, keyVaultKey.Properties.ReleasePolicy.EncodedPolicy.ToString() is throwing a System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object.

On Azure.Security.KeyVault.Keys 4.5.0, there is no issue with this code path

### Expected behavior

keyVaultKey.Properties.ReleasePolicy.EncodedPolicy.ToString() returns the stringified release policy

### Actual behavior

keyVaultKey.Properties.ReleasePolicy.EncodedPolicy.ToString() is throwing a System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an instance of an object

### Reproduction Steps

string keyName = &#34;someKeyName&#34;;
string? version = null;

Azure.Security.KeyVault.Keys.KeyClient client = some valid mhsm keyclient;

KeyVaultKey keyVaultKey = await client.GetKeyAsync(keyName, version).ConfigureAwait(false);

KeyReleasePolicy hsmKeyReleasePolicy = keyVaultKey.Properties.ReleasePolicy;

if (hsmKeyReleasePolicy == null)
{
    throw new InvalidOperationException($&#34;Failed to get release policy for key=[REDACTED] 
hsmKeyReleasePolicy.EncodedPolicy.ToString(); // This is where the code throws the null ref exception

